'''Steven Thomas Finn''' (born [[4 April]] [[1989]] [[Watford]], [[Hertfordshire]]) is an [[English (people)|English]] [[cricketer]].

Finn is a [[batsman|right-handed batsman]] and a [[seam bowler|right-arm fast-medium bowler]].  He is a member of the Middlesex Cricket Academy.

Finn made his [[first-class cricket|first-class]] debut for [[Middlesex County Cricket Club|Middlesex]] on [[1 June]] [[2005]], playing against [[Cambridge UCCE]] at [[Fenner's]].[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/82/82364.html]  He took 1-16 and 1-37, but did not bat.  He was Middlesex's youngest debutant since [[Fred Titmus]] in 1949.  Fellow 16-year-old debutant [[Billy Godleman]] (born [[11 February]] [[1989]]) also beat Titmus' record in the same match.  Finn went on to play for the Middlesex [[second XI]] in 2005 and 2006.

Finn toured South Africa with the England Under-16 squad in 2005.  He played in two Under-19 Test matches and three Under-19 ODIs against the Indian side that toured England in 2006, and in seven Under-19 ODIs in Malaysia in early 2007.  He says he models himself on [[Glen McGrath]]. {{Fact|date=April 2007}}

